 ENGLISH:
=== === === === === === === === === === === === === === === === === === ===
The files in this directory ARE NOT a part of the METATYPE1 package,
although they are either use it or are used by it.

   The ``extra'' directory contains the epsincl package for embedding
   external EPSes into files generated by METAPOST. The package
   is distributed separately and can be used independently of
   the METATYPE1 package. It has been included here because the METATYPE1
   package makes use of it for including ``stencils'' (useful for making
   replicas of traditional fonts). The package epsincl consists of:
      epsincl.mp  -- METAPOST macros; the main macros is use_eps(EPS_name)
                     returning an object of a picture type; the file
                     should be placed somewhere in the path searched
                     by METAPOST
      epsincl.bat -- batch file; its parameter is a name of an EPS file
                     to which the external EPSes are to be inserted;
                     W A R N I N G: the command lines in which GAWK is
                     invoked may need some adjustments (e.g., specifying
                     explicitly the directory where epsincl.awk is stored)
      epsincl.awk -- AWK script -- performs the main job of the inserting
                     of the external EPSes

-- README: this file

The package epsincl requires GAWK (we still use ver. 3.0.3), 
and METAPOST.

The fonts generated by pf2mt1 are a good example of using
the METATYPE1 package, although they do not make use of 
possibilities it offers (in particular, the resulting fonts
are not parameterized).

